{"id":572687,"title":"Laughter Against The Machine","description":"<p><strong><em>Laughter Against The Machine</em></strong> is a seven part documentary series following comedians W. Kamau Bell, Nato Green, and Janine Brito as they journey across the U.S. in 2011 before and after Occupy protests rock the nation.</p><p>The trio visits some of the least funny places in the world, like the militarized US/Mexico border, the 9th Ward in New Orleans that was devastated by Hurricane Katrina, or Oakland under martial law during Occupy. Amidst this grim political backdrop, the comics try and help their audiences unwind between being teargassed by cops or arrested for blocking ICE deportations.</p><p><br></p><p>Released in 2020</p>","short_description":null,"duration":"00:00","video_count":7,"active_stream":false,"content_type":"collection","main_poster":"https://alpha.uscreencdn.com/images/programs/572687/horizontal/7507_2Fcatalog_image_2F572687_2FE6uopBSAQHKqm91hLvyG_LATM_20ORIGINAL_20CORNER_202.jpg","url":"/programs/latm","slider_video_hls":null,"main_poster_featured":"https://alpha.uscreencdn.com/images/programs/572687/horizontal/big_7507_2Fcatalog_image_2F572687_2FE6uopBSAQHKqm91hLvyG_LATM_20ORIGINAL_20CORNER_202.jpg","author_id":null,"main_poster_hybrid":"https://alpha.uscreencdn.com/images/programs/572687/horizontal/small_7507_2Fcatalog_image_2F572687_2FE6uopBSAQHKqm91hLvyG_LATM_20ORIGINAL_20CORNER_202.jpg","main_poster_featured_hybrid":"https://alpha.uscreencdn.com/images/programs/572687/horizontal/big_7507_2Fcatalog_image_2F572687_2FE6uopBSAQHKqm91hLvyG_LATM_20ORIGINAL_20CORNER_202.jpg","permalink":"latm","extended":true,"featured_category_image":null,"duration_in_seconds":null,"children_videos":[{"id":572685,"permalink":"latm1"},{"id":572684,"permalink":"latm2"},{"id":572683,"permalink":"latm3"},{"id":572680,"permalink":"latm4"},{"id":572686,"permalink":"latm5"},{"id":572681,"permalink":"latm6"},{"id":572688,"permalink":"latm7"}],"meta_title":"Laughter Against The M